    <item>
      <title>SpaceX Acquires xAI for $250 Billion — The Largest Merger in History, Then Loses Every Co-Founder</title>
      <link>https://chatforest.com/guides/spacex-xai-250-billion-merger-largest-in-history/</link>
      <guid>https://chatforest.com/guides/spacex-xai-250-billion-merger-largest-in-history/</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 07 Apr 2026 23:00:00 &#43;0000</pubDate>
      <description>SpaceX acquired Elon Musk&#39;s xAI in February 2026 for $250 billion, creating a $1.25 trillion combined entity — the largest corporate merger by valuation in history. The deal is structured around &#39;orbital data centers&#39; that integrate Grok AI into Starlink&#39;s satellite network. But within weeks, all 11 original xAI co-founders departed. Musk acknowledged xAI &#39;wasn&#39;t built right&#39; and announced a full rebuild. In April, SpaceX filed confidentially for a $1.75 trillion IPO targeting $75 billion — the largest public offering ever attempted. Musk is also requiring IPO banks to purchase Grok subscriptions. This analysis covers the merger structure, the co-founder exodus, xAI&#39;s market position (17.8% US chatbot share, $2B projected 2026 revenue), the IPO filing, and the honest limitations of every claim.</description>
    </item>
    
